<http://example.org/pt#stmt/165> prov:value "Concern was raised about the safety of the Tube, given the derailment at Chancery Lane earlier in 2003.[96] A joint report by the Underground and report maintenance contractor Tube Lines concluded that poor track geometry was the main cause, and therefore extra friction arising out of striations (scratches) on a newly installed set of points had allowed the leading wheel of the last carriage to climb the rail and derail.",
