<http://example.org/pt#stmt/6> prov:value "0 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService true isFarePaying true isScheduledService true modeName \"bus\" 1 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.",
        "Fare zones See also: London fare zones § Ancillary zones London Underground and Docklands Light Railway use Transport for London's London fare zones to calculate fares, including fares on the Underground only.",
        "James's Park\", \"Victoria\", \"Sloane Square\", \"South Kensington\", \"Gloucester Road\", \"Earl's Court\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Wimbledon branch (from Earl's Court)\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Earl's Court\", \"West Kensington\", \"Barons Court\", \"Hammersmith\", \"Ravenscourt Park\", \"Stamford Brook\", \"Turnham Green\", \"Gunnersbury\", \"Kew Gardens\", \"Richmond\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Wimbledon branch (via Wimbledon)\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Turnham Green\", \"Chiswick Park\", \"Gunnersbury\", \"Kew Gardens\", \"Richmond\", \"East Putney\", \"Putney Bridge\", \"Parsons Green\", \"Fulham Broadway\", \"West Brompton\", \"Earl's Court\", \"Wimbledon\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Ealing Broadway branch\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Earl's Court\", \"Kensington (Olympia)\", \"Ealing Broadway\", \"Turnham Green\", \"Acton Town\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Edgware Road branch\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Edgware Road\", \"Paddington\", \"Bayswater\", \"Notting Hill Gate\", \"High Street Kensington\", \"Earl's Court\" ] } ] }, { \"name\": \"Elizabeth line\", \"colour\": \"purple\", \"branches\": [ { \"branch\": \"Western (Reading/Heathrow to Paddington)\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Reading\", \"Twyford\", \"Maidenhead\", \"Taplow\", \"Burnham\", \"Slough\", \"Langley\", \"Iver\", \"West Drayton\", \"Hayes & Harlington\", \"Southall\", \"Hanwell\", \"West Ealing\", \"Ealing Broadway\", \"Acton Main Line\", \"Paddington\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Heathrow spur\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Heathrow Terminal 5\", \"Heathrow Terminals 2 & 3\", \"Heathrow Terminal 4\", \"Hayes & Harlington\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Central tunnel (Paddington to Abbey Wood)\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Paddington\", \"Bond Street\", \"Tottenham Court Road\", \"Farringdon\", \"City Thameslink\", \"Liverpool Street\", \"Whitechapel\", \"Canary Wharf\", \"Custom House\", \"Woolwich\", \"Abbey Wood\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Eastern (Liverpool Street to Shenfield)\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Liverpool Street\", \"Stratford\", \"Maryland\", \"Forest Gate\", \"Manor Park\", \"Ilford\", \"Seven Kings\", \"Goodmayes\", \"Chadwell Heath\", \"Romford\", \"Gidea Park\", \"Harold Wood\", \"Brentwood\", \"Shenfield\" ] } ] }, { \"name\": \"Hammersmith & City line\", \"colour\": \"pink\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Hammersmith\", \"Goldhawk Road\", \"Shepherd's Bush Market\", \"Wood Lane\", \"Latimer Road\", \"Ladbroke Grove\", \"Westbourne Park\", \"Royal Oak\", \"Paddington\", \"Edgware Road\", \"Baker Street\", \"Great Portland Street\", \"Euston Square\", \"King's Cross St.",
        "Northern line 1995 Stock arrives at Stockwell tube station heading northbound to Edgware via Bank, July 2024 Overview Termini Kennington, Battersea Power Station, Morden Edgware, High Barnet, Mill Hill East Stations 52 Colour on map Black Website tfl.gov.uk/tube/route/northern/ Edit this at Wikidata Service Type Rapid transit System London Underground Depot(s) Golders GreenMorden Stabling Sidings: HighgateEdgwareHigh Barnet[1] Rolling stock 1995 Stock Ridership 339.7 million passenger journeys (2019)[2] History Opened 18 December 1890; 135 years ago (as City and South London Railway) 22 June 1907; 118 years ago (as Charing Cross, Euston & Hampstead Railway) 13 September 1926; 99 years ago (Lines merged) 28 August 1937; 88 years ago (Renamed to Northern line) Last extension 20 September 2021; 4 years ago Technical Line length 58 km (36 mi) Character Deep-tube Track gauge 1,435 mm (4 ft 8+1⁄2 in) standard gauge Electrification Fourth rail, 630 V DC Operating speed 45 mph (72 km/h)[3] Signalling CBTC (SelTrac) Transport for London rail lines The Northern line is a London Underground line that runs between North London and South London.",
        "Some National Rail stations and almost all Transport for London served stations outside Greater London in the home counties of Buckinghamshire, Essex, Hertfordshire and Surrey are either included in fare zones 4, 5 or 6 or in extended zones beyond these.",
        "Unlike London's deep-level lines, the Circle line tunnels are just below the surface and are of similar size to those on British main lines.",
        "line runs services on dedicated infrastructure in central London from the Great Western Main Line west of Paddington station to Abbey Wood and via Whitechapel to the Great Eastern Main Line near Stratford; and out parallel to the Great Eastern Main Line to Shenfield in the east, along the Great Western Main Line to Reading and Heathrow Airport in the west." .

<http://example.org/pt#stmt/60> prov:value "5+7, 8+9 etc.",
        "In the case of the Morden–Edgware, these were the London and North Eastern Railway (LNER) suburban lines north of Highgate, built in the 1860s and 1870s by the Edgware, Highgate and London Railway (EH&LR) and Railway successors, running from Finsbury Park to Edgware via Highgate, with branches to Alexandra Palace and High Barnet.",
        "Route map of zonal system of the railway services directly managed by Transport for London. Stations only served by National Rail services are not shown in this map. Rail service fares in Greater Lond",
        "The bombs killed 15 people, including the two suicide bombers.[28][29] Following the attacks, the whole of the Circle line was closed until 8 August.[30] A day before a ban on drinking alcohol on public transport in London came into force, a party was held on 31 May 2008, mainly on the Circle line.",
        "These services were augmented by a new central section in May 2022, and rebranded as the Elizabeth line.",
