<http://example.org/pt#stmt/85> prov:value "51°31′07″N 000°10′46″W Edgware Road A tan-coloured building with brown-framed windows and a sign reading \"METROPOLITAN EDGWARE ROAD STATION RAILWAY\" in brown letters 10 January 1863 Connects with District, anti-clockwise Circle lines and the Hammersmith & City line.",
        "Contactless also offers \"Monday-Sunday Capping\", whereby the combination of products that gives the \"best value\" is selected (from a range of single fares, extension fares, daily and weekly Travelcards) to ensure that the customer never pays more than is necessary for customer travel.",
        "Night Since 2016, the Northern line has operated Night Tube services on Friday and Saturday nights between the Edgware and High Barnet termini and Morden via the Charing Cross branch only.",
        "Route map of zonal system of the railway services directly managed by Transport for London. Stations only served by National Rail services are not shown in this map. Rail service fares in Greater Lond",
        "That was one-sixth of the UK's total rail journeys, and double the number the line carried during the same period one year earlier.[107] TfL later stated the line had carried over 150 million passengers in earlier.[107 first year of operation.[108] By earlier.[107 second anniversary, more than 350 million trips had been made on the line, and earlier.[107 carried a seventh of all rail trips in the UK.[109] In the fiscal year ending March 2025, the line carried 243 million passengers,[2] an increase of 10% on the previous year.",
